    "en": {
      "title": "Magammana fire and one year old daughter also dies",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "According to Kahathuduwa police, the six-year-old daughter who was receiving treatment at Borella Ridgeway Arya Children's Hospital has also died after suffering burns in a fire that broke out in a room on the ground floor of a two-storey house in Magammana area of \u200b\u200bHomagama on the 25th night.",
        "The police say that the deceased was a six-year-old daughter named Ritushi Ranasinghe who lived in Homagama Magammana.",
        "The fire took place on the 25th at around 8.30 pm in a room on the ground floor of a two-storied house in Homagama Magammana area.",
        "At the time of the incident, the deceased six-year-old daughter's mother, father and elder sister were inside the room and they were admitted to Homagama Base Hospital and Colombo National Hospital for treatment.",
        "The father of the six-year-old daughter died on the same day, the mother died the next day and the elder sister died three days after the incident.",
        "Lasantha Buddhika 47, (father) Kalika Devi 35, (mother) and Kavindi Ranasinghe 19, (elder sister) died in this fire and the last rites of their dead bodies were held at Diyagama Flower Hall.",
        "The injured six-year-old daughter died while undergoing treatment at the Lady Ridgeway Children's Hospital and a post-mortem examination was conducted."
      ],
